{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSourceFuncs"},{"text":" struct contains a table of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"functions used to handle event sources in a generic manner."}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","topicSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs\/init(_:)-17j5x","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs\/init(_:)-5njpw","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs\/init(_:)-5qwlr","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs\/init(_:)-7tzdq","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs\/init(_:)-q1vp","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs\/init(opaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs\/init(raw:)-320me","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs\/init(raw:)-ho2f","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs\/init(retaining:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs\/init(retainingCPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs\/init(retainingOpaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs\/init(retainingRaw:)-3r0wf","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs\/init(retainingRaw:)-m0x8"],"title":"Initializers","anchor":"Initializers"},{"anchor":"Instance-Properties","title":"Instance Properties","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs\/ptr"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs\/SourceFuncsProtocol-Implementations"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Default-Implementations","title":"Default Implementations"}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib11SourceFuncsC","title":"SourceFuncs","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"SourceFuncs","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SourceFuncs","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Class","symbolKind":"class"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SourceFuncs"}]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For idle sources, the prepare and check functions always return "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to indicate that the source is always ready to be processed. The prepare","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"function also returns a timeout value of 0 to ensure that the "},{"code":"poll()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" call","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"doesn’t block (since that would be time wasted which could have been spent","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"running the idle function)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For timeout sources, the prepare and check functions both return "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"if the timeout interval has expired. The prepare function also returns"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a timeout value to ensure that the "},{"code":"poll()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" call doesn’t block too long"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and miss the next timeout.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For file descriptor sources, the prepare function typically returns "},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"since it must wait until "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"poll()"},{"type":"text","text":" has been called before it knows whether"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"any events need to be processed. It sets the returned timeout to -1 to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"indicate that it doesn’t mind how long the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"poll()"},{"type":"text","text":" call blocks. In the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"check function, it tests the results of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"poll()"},{"type":"text","text":" call to see if the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"required condition has been met, and returns "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" if so.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" type acts as an owner of an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSourceFuncs"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" as a strong reference or owner of a ","type":"text"},{"code":"GSourceFuncs","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" (instead of ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Sou